-- CGGVeritas Reports Quarterly Profit From Year-Earlier Loss; Orders Stable
-- David Whitehouse
-- 2010-07-30T03:59:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/cggveritas-reports-quarterly-profit-from-year-earlier-loss-orders-stable.html

          
          
             CGGVeritas, the world’s largest
seismic surveyor of oilfields, reported second-quarter net
income of $8 million versus a year-earlier loss of $32 million.  
 The order book was stable at July 1 at $1.5 billion, the
company said in a statement published in France’s La Tribune
newspaper.  
          
          


  


        